Here are some projects I'm proud of working on.

### [MOSES](https://github.com/ganglab-bnl/MOSES)

A foundational algorithm applying the group theoretic concept of 'symmetry' to chemical engineering. An information-minimizing method for to designing self-assembling DNA origami nanoparticle lattices. Under supervision of Dr. Jason Kahn at Brookhaven and Dr. Oleg Gang at Columbia University. Our paper was accepted to ACS Nano!

### [Synchrony](https://github.com/hyuncat/Synchrony)

An opinionated practice tool for musicians, which compares a user's recording to a MIDI score and computes the user's mistakes in real-time. Uses a probabilistic pitch detection method that utilizes the MIDI to detect note events. Under supervision of the kind NYU professor Dennis Shasha.

<img src="/assets/images/projects/synchrony.png" alt="synchrony" width="500"/>

### [RichCluster](https://github.com/hyuncat/RichCluster)

An Rcpp library for performing hierarchical clustering on multiple enriched genomics datasets. Clusters different biological 'terms' based on overlapping gene content. Coded in C++ for fast clustering, with customizable linkage / distance metrics and supporting visualizations. (Paper-in-progress)

<img src="https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/114366569/423184573-f5c857bc-8547-445f-be15-b9a1102f76f4.jpeg?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..DbtK5c3l9FhePGHWzjIl45jbQBkcC4ZBFUmjxvv1Qco" alt="synchrony" width="400"/>

### [Pre-Walkwise](https://github.com/hyuncat/pre-walkwise)

Scripts and web app to implement and visualize Kalman filtering and Map-Matching algorithms for GPS time-series data. For use in preprocessing the training data for Caspar Lant's (Columbia CS PhD.) Walkwise model, which predicts pedestrian intent at intersections.

<img src="https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/114366569/350583091-d382c725-6dd0-45cb-8b14-05223faeb18b.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJnaXRodWIuY29tIiwiYXVkIjoicmF3LmdpdGh1YnVzZXJjb250ZW50LmNvbSIsImtleSI6ImtleTUiLCJleHAiOjE3NDI2NjI2MTgsIm5iZiI6MTc0MjY2MjMxOCwicGF0aCI6Ii8xMTQzNjY1NjkvMzUwNTgzMDkxLWQzODJjNzI1LTZkZDAtNDVjYi04YjE0LTA1MjIzZmFlYjE4Yi5wbmc_.exWR7cMmA1mRqmSvgjOpGFk1MrunR3ZPi-Nb1HpfKjg" alt="walkwise" width="500"/>

### [daily-integral](https://github.com/hyuncat/daily-integral)

<img src="https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/114366569/328767144-a45a84da-5b8f-4513-8884-7ffd2ce80665.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJnaXRodWIuY29tIiwiYXVkIjoicmF3LmdpdGh1YnVzZXJjb250ZW50LmNvbSIsImtleSI6ImtleTUiLCJleHAiOjE3NDI2NjI2NTAsIm5iZiI6MTc0MjY2MjM1MCwicGF0aCI6Ii8xMTQzNjY1NjkvMzI4NzY3MTQ0LWE0NWE4NGRhLTViOGYtNDUxMy04ODg0LTdmZmQyY2U4MDY2NS5wbmc_.PrsTso-P-Wd8MzYQO9OWgWE56cK1tDVQPSbncdecAYY" alt="" width="300"/>

Solve a new integral every day, and compete against friends on a daily leaderboard. Created with React and MongoDB backend with secure user authentication. 

I hosted the site using Vercel [daily-integral.vercel.app](here) and created a video demo of it for my web development class at Columbia.
